cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CL

1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with scene understanding and human-object interaction detection using visual cues and contextual information. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper involves machine learning techniques for inferring interactions and leveraging semantic regularities. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper involves developing a dual-graph attention network for effective aggregation of contextual information. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper deals with understanding human-object interactions, which is relevant to robotics applications. 
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a less likely category but possible as the paper involves leveraging semantic information for improving inference.
